HEADWORD: Steam up
<hw>Steam` up"</hw> <pr>(st⟦emac⟧m` ⟦ucr⟧p")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<def>To cause to be covered by a translucent layer of condensed water in
fine droplets, such as by breathing on a cold window; to fog; <as>as, to
<ex>steam up</ex> one's eyeglasses</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steamy</ent>⟦br⟧
